From Dennis Holt Subject Re Honda clutch chatter In article Doug Zolmer writes In article James Bruder writes anyone else experiencing a similar problem This concerns the clutch on a Honda Accord When the clutch is first used in the morning about the first miles of shifting there is a significant amount of clutch chatter until things warm Then the clutch shifts This chatter started when I moved to the San Francisco Bay area from a low humidity The dealer stated that this is known to happen since Honda changed from an asbestos to non asbestos clutch No remedy Seems that moisture on clutch surface causes slipping until the moisture Any comments out there The clutch on my ' Honda Civic EX V EX in the does this It's Now that I think about it is worse when the humidity is The dealer also claims there's nothing they can do since the clutch is a self adjusting hydraulic design Yeah One of the reasons I sold my ' Civic VX was the chattery grabby clutch although I din't notice it being any worse in humid weather perhaps because its always humid around I was told by Honda that it has to do with changing from asbestos to non asbestos linings which began around Someone could make some good money selling the old fashion variety if it's legal to manufacture them these My feeling is that since many other car makers do not have this problem that it's a poor design or engineering problem on the part of Three things to look out for on all Honda products clutch chatter bad brake rotors and rusty exhaust